genresAdvancedInfo.name: belgian jazz
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Belgian jazz is a genre that combines traditional jazz elements with the unique cultural influences found in Belgium. It often features improvisation and complex harmonies, and has been influenced by both American and European jazz traditions.
